    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TV26">
<l>nāṉilam vāykkoṇṭu naṉṉī raṟameṉṟu kōtukoṇṭa</l>
<l>vēṉilañ celvaṉ cuvaittumiḻ pālai kaṭantapoṉṉē</l>
<l>kāṉilan tōyntuviṇ ṇōrtoḻuṅ kaṇṇaṉveḵ kāvutampūn</l>
<l>tēṉiḷañ cōlaiyap pālatep pālaikkuñ cēmattatē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The gold for which [you] crossed the desert that has been tasted [and] spit out by the summer walker (~ the sun)</l>
<l>who took fault with the words “taking good water to the four grounds is duty”,</l>
<l>will it have a share in the good groves with honey [and] wet flowers, Veḵkā of Kaṇṇaṉ,</l>
<l>who is worshipped by the celestials, touching the ground at [his] feet, will it be a protection from any desert?</l>
<l></l>
<l>b (traditional)</l>
<l>O gold[-girl] who crossed the desert tasted [and] spit out by the lord of sunlight</l>
<l>who had taken the four grounds in [his] mouth, chewed them, so that the good water was finished [and] taken the reminder,</l>
<l>over there is Veḵkā of Kaṇṇaṉ, who is worshipped by the celestials touching the ground with [their] feet. It has a share</l>
<l>of good groves with honey [and] pretty flowers. It will be a protection from any desert.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
